# create a single view app

create a single view ios app. choose the language is swift. select none for Test Options.

# add a button to the view

Add one button object to the Main.Storyboard.
when you add a button object, you need to add constraints for the object. The the system can know the position on the screen.

In the right bottom, the third button is the align constraints, that can make the object place the center of the screen. 

1. Horizontally in Container : the center of the X axis.
2. Vertically in Container : the center of the Y axis.

the config value is the offset of the center of the axis.

you can set the multipler in the Size inspector. then can set the object in the 1/4 of the axis.